H, Postumus, my Postumus, Fast glide the years, nor pious breath Wards wrinkles and old age from us, Nor yet indomitable death:

No, friend, tho' thrice a hundred kine To tearless Pluto daily bled,

Whose ambient, gruesome waves confine, Vast Geryon, the triple dread,

And Tityos-the waves that all Whom bounteous earth provides with food Must voyage o'er nor hope recall, Tho' men of wealth, tho' delvers rude.
